33#include <sys/cdefs.h>
34#ifndef lint
35__RCSID("$NetBSD: print-sunatm.c,v 1.6 2017/02/05 04:05:05 spz Exp $");
36#endif
37
38/* \summary: SunATM DLPI capture printer */
39
40#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
41#include "config.h"
42#endif
43
44#include <netdissect-stdinc.h>
45
46struct mbuf;
47struct rtentry;
48
49#include "netdissect.h"
50#include "extract.h"
51
52#include "atm.h"
53
54/* SunATM header for ATM packet */
55#define DIR_POS 0 /* Direction (0x80 = transmit, 0x00 = receive) */
56#define VPI_POS 1 /* VPI */
57#define VCI_POS 2 /* VCI */
58#define PKT_BEGIN_POS 4 /* Start of the ATM packet */
59
60/* Protocol type values in the bottom for bits of the byte at SUNATM_DIR_POS. */
61#define PT_LANE 0x01 /* LANE */
62#define PT_LLC 0x02 /* LLC encapsulation */
63
64/*
65 * This is the top level routine of the printer. 'p' points
66 * to the SunATM pseudo-header for the packet, 'h->ts' is the timestamp,
67 * 'h->len' is the length of the packet off the wire, and 'h->caplen'
68 * is the number of bytes actually captured.
69 */
70u_int
71sunatm_if_print(netdissect_options *ndo,
72 const struct pcap_pkthdr *h, const u_char *p)
73{
74 u_int caplen = h->caplen;
75 u_int length = h->len;
76 u_short vci;
77 u_char vpi;
78 u_int traftype;
79
80 if (caplen < PKT_BEGIN_POS) {
81 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[|atm]"));
82 return (caplen);
83 }
84
85 if (ndo->ndo_eflag) {
86 ND_PRINT((ndo, p[DIR_POS] & 0x80 ? "Tx: " : "Rx: "));
87 }
88
89 switch (p[DIR_POS] & 0x0f) {
90
91 case PT_LANE:
92 traftype = ATM_LANE;
93 break;
94
95 case PT_LLC:
96 traftype = ATM_LLC;
97 break;
98
99 default:
100 traftype = ATM_UNKNOWN;
101 break;
102 }
103
104 vci = EXTRACT_16BITS(&p[VCI_POS]);
105 vpi = p[VPI_POS];
106
107 p += PKT_BEGIN_POS;
108 caplen -= PKT_BEGIN_POS;
109 length -= PKT_BEGIN_POS;
110 atm_print(ndo, vpi, vci, traftype, p, length, caplen);
111
112 return (PKT_BEGIN_POS);
113}
